	‚ÄúMost kids go for the low hanging fruit, liberal art degrees and the like,‚Äù she added. ‚ÄúHow&#039;d you end up wanting to become a chef?‚Äù
	‚ÄúI guess it runs in my family,‚Äù Matt replied with a shrug. ‚ÄúMy parents have always worked in the food industry, and as you already know, they own this diner. I always had a knack for cooking, and I thought that I might as well make a go of it. Earning a living doing what they love is everyone&#039;s dream, right?‚Äù
